<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11001f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11001f">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11001f"> 1(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> whispers (ka&ntilde;on)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Gunpowder has never reached these simple folks, and the hunting is all done on tiptoe with silent poisoned arrows. They plead that one bang from a gun would be too tell-tale, booming along the valley. These <mark>ca&ntilde;ons of theirs are whispering galleries</mark>, that, with a great awakening clang, echo and re-echo the secret of even the hunter&apos;s footfall. <small> Daniel Crawford, <a name="DCTB2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DCTB2"><cite title="source">Thinking Black</cite></a> (1912) 353</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n10146e" href="n10all.htm#n10146e">N10 (VI.B.16):146(e)</a>.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c04028f" href="c4all.htm#c04028f">VI.C.04:028(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
